d the words of Laban’s sons, saying, Jacob hath taken away all that was our father’s; and of that which was our father’s hath he gotten all this glory.","year":-1739},{"id":"rec3O2VWrMQIJzMZE","ref":"Gen.31.2","text":"And Jacob beheld the countenance of Laban, and, behold, it was not toward him as before.","year":-1739},{"id":"recqGE8gPxyFutlB1","ref":"Gen.31.3","text":"And the LORD said unto Jacob, Return unto the land of thy fathers, and to thy kindred; and I will be with thee.","year":-1739},{"id":"rec4UDnrUHXhHCyaX","ref":"Gen.31.4","text":"And Jacob sent and called Rachel and Leah to the field unto his flock,","year":-1739},{"id":"recNsxF7uLLWmGKFa","ref":"Gen.31.5","text":"And said unto them, I see your father’s countenance, that it is not toward me as before; but the God of my father hath been with me.","year":-1739},{"id":"recn6TbBF9oulGhV5","ref":"Gen.31.6","text":"And ye know that with all my power I have served your father.","year":-1739},{"id":"recw83nD1xklKz8wQ","ref":"Gen.31.7","text":"And your father hath deceived me, and changed my wages ten times; but God suffered him not to hurt me.","year":-1739},{"id":"rec9yh7oTHgkNlt97","ref":"Gen.31.8","text":"If he said thus, The speckled shall be thy wages; then all the cattle bare speckled: and if he said thus, The ringstraked shall be thy hire; then bare all the cattle ringstraked.","year":-1739}]}
